Preconditions:
- The input array `arr` is not null.
- The length of the input array `arr` is greater than 0.
- The input array `arr` represents a permutation of the integers in the range `[0, n - 1]`.
- All elements in the input array `arr` are unique.

Postconditions:
- The return value is an integer representing the largest number of chunks that can be made to sort the array.
- The chunks are individually sorted.
- After concatenating the sorted chunks, the result is equal to the sorted array.